    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-12-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="551"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d551">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Lithuania/94</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Lithuanian Minister (<persName corresp="#p_BBK1"
                            type="from">Balutis</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-15">December 15,
                            1932</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my note and Memorandum delivered to
                    you on December 10, and the exchange of views on that occasion, I have the honor
                    to inform you that the Lithuanian Government has decided to pay the next
                    instalment due to the Treasury of the United States on December 15, as provided
                    by the terms of the Debt Funding Agreement of September 22, 1924, and that the
                    said payment will be made to the Secretary of the Treasury of the United
                    States.</p>
                <p>At the same time my Government desires to express a hope that by making this
                    payment it is not placing itself in a less favorable <pb facs="0919" n="799"
                        xml:id="pg_799"/> position than that which may result to any of the other
                    countries from the eventual reconsideration of the general question of
                    intergovernmental debts.</p>
                <p>Please accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BBK1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bronius K. Balutis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
